Interface Promise.OnRejectedCallback<NV>

  • Type Parameters:
    NV - Type of the value returned by the callback, which will be used to resolve the next promise in the chain.
    Enclosing interface:
    Promise<V>

    public static interface Promise.OnRejectedCallback<NV>
    Callback interface for rejected promises.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.util.concurrent.Future<NV> onRejected(java.lang.Exception reason)
      The promise on which this callback was registered has been rejected.

    • Method Detail

      • onRejected

        java.util.concurrent.Future<NV> onRejected(java.lang.Exception reason)
                                           throws java.lang.Exception
        The promise on which this callback was registered has been rejected.
        Parameters:
        reason - The exception that caused the promise to be rejected.
        Returns:
        A direct value (wrapped in a Value.wrap(Object), a new Promise or any other kind of Future.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Any exception thrown by this method will lead to the rejection of the next promise in the chain.
